#Text=Wikinews interviews Daylight Saving for South East Queensland Party about the upcoming Queensland State election
#Text=Friday , January 30 , 2009
#Text=With a Queensland state election coming up in Australia , many minor parties will be looking to hold balance of power and making the major parties listen to what they have to say .
#Text=Daylight Saving for South East Queensland ( DS4SEQ ) is one of these parties .
#Text=DS4SEQ is a single issue party which , as its name suggests , advocates the implementation of daylight saving in South East Queensland .
#Text=Currently Queensland runs on Australian Eastern Standard Time ( UTC+10 ) .
#Text=Queensland 's unicameral parliament is due for election in September , but may be held earlier .
#Text=The election , like all Australian elections , must be held on a Saturday .
#Text=The election campaign will run for a minimum of twenty six ( 26 ) days and a maximum of fifty six following the issue of the writs .
#Text=Wikinews held an exclusive interview with the DS4SEQ .
#Text=Answering on behalf of the party was leader Jason Furze .
#Text=Interview
#Text=Why do you want to form government ?
#Text=DS4SEQ would like to gain a sizeable percentage of the primary vote and win a number of seats .

#Text=As we are a single issue party , voting for us will send a clear message to the major parties and that is : when it comes to the issue of daylight saving , the people of South East Queensland have ben [ sic ] ignored for too long , and a dual time zone arrangement must be implemented .
#Text=What are the three main policies you will take into this election ?

#Text=DS4SEQ is a single issue political party , with the sole policy being : to have Daylight Saving Time introduced into the South East Queensland region , under a dual time zone arrangement aligned to Australian Eastern Daylight Time .
#Text=Daylight Saving is a lifestyle and business choice and one that the majority of South East Queenslanders would like to have .

#Text=We acknowledge that there are many important issues facing the State of Queensland , however , DS4SEQ do not believe that this is a valid reason to ignore the majority voice who support daylight saving .
#Text=A map of South East Queensland , the area where DS4SEQ want Daylight Saving Time .
#Text=Other Councils included in the area are Gondiwindi , Southern Downs , Toowoomba ( to the southwest ) and Gympie ( to the north } .
#Text=Image : MagpieShooter .
#Text=How will you address these policies ?
#Text=The dual time zone concept that DS4SEQ is proposing is a well thought out compromise to the current situation that obviously does not work .

#Text=The dual time zone boundary is formed by the inclusion of 15 local council areas and provides a respectful view towards regional and rural Queenslanders , whilst also giving consideration to the view of the majority of residents in South East Queensland .

#Text=This will allow regional and rural Queensland to continue to operate on Australian Eastern Standard time , whilst the South East Queensland region adopts Daylight Saving Time for 6 months of the year .
#Text=If you ca n't form government , who would you like to see do so ?
#Text=DS4SEQ do not offer an opinion of which Party may form the next State Government .

#Text=However , what we would like to see , is for both major parties to change their thinking about Daylight Saving in Queensland , and seriously consider a dual time zone arrangement for 6 months of the year .
#Text=What should Queenslanders keep in mind , when heading to the polls ?
#Text=Vote # 1 DS4SEQ and number 2 whicher [ sic ] party you would like to govern the state .

#Text=Voting DS4SEQ number 1 , will not be a wasted vote , because if the Party gains a sizeable percentage of the primary vote , winning a few seats along the way , this will allow us to convince the major parties to change their thinking on the issue of daylight saving .
#Text=As demonstrated by the 2007 Queensland Government research , about 70 % of constituents within South East Queensland are in favour of daylight saving .
#Text=State-wide , those who are against are now the minority , and mostly reside in the regional and rural districts outside of the DS4SEQ proposed daylight saving region .

#Text=It has been 17 years since the people of Queensland have had a say on daylight saving , and in this time there has been a major shift in community attitudes demonstrating an increase in support .
#Text=" It 's About Time ! "
#Text=that the people of South East Queensland had a voice on this issue .
#Text=South East Queensland we are your voice , and " It 's About Time ! "
